Introduction

  • In this LAB we have conducted data visualization on the data which consists of different Signal Strength and ASU's reading taken at various places within BIAS campus and througout the Bhimtal Lake
  • The devices used were different models of phones such as Samsung, Vivo etc, and the sim used were Airtel, JIO and VI for the devices
  • First we import the CSV's files containing data within Bhimtal Lake.
  • Then we installed the following libraries :
    1. matplotlib and seaborn to visualize our data
    2. pandas to clean and process data
  • After that we do some data cleaning using pandas , for eg:
    1. Renaming the coloumn name so that we can process them.
    2. Removing the decimal values so that we can plot graph out of them .
    3. Removing NaN and Null values to remove discrepancy.
  • After that We have performed the data visualization.

Procedure

  N=N-1

    plt.text(row['Location Name'], row['asu1'], f'Avg: {row["asu1"]:.2f}', ha='left', va='bottom')

# Adding labels and title
plt.xlabel('Location')
plt.ylabel('ASU')
plt.title('Comparison of ASU and Average ASU for class Data and our Data')

# Adding a legend
plt.legend()

# Show the plot
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()
